               <p>The Prosecutor depos'd, That the Prisoner (a <rs id="t17310428-75-deflabel380" type="occupation">Lad</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17310428-75-defend433 t17310428-75-deflabel380"></join> of about 12 Years of Age) was employ'd by him to go of Errands, and look after his Shop; that he went out at about 11 o'Clock, left the Prisoner in the Parlour, and returning between 2 and 3, found his Parlour and Shop Door open, and the Till broken open, and his Money was gone; that going in Quest of the Prisoner, he apprehended him, and found the Money upon him, except one Guinea he had chang'd.</p>
